{{Birth-date and age|1998}}<ref name=\"Bio\">{{cite web |title=Sunny Malik (Indian Idol) Wiki, Age, Girlfriend, Family, Biography & More \u2013 WikiBio |url=https://wikibio.in/sunny-malik/ |accessdate=7 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place      = Amarpura, [[Bhatinda]], [[India]]\n| death_date       = <!-- {{death date and age|df=yes|deathyear|mm|dd|birthyear|mm|dd}} -->\n| death_place      = \n| instrument       = vocals\n| genre            = {{Flatlist|\n*[[Sufi music|Sufi]]\n*Rock}}\n| occupation       = Singer\n| years_active     = 2020-present\n| label            = [[T-Series]]\n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = <!-- {{URL|website}} -->\n}}\n'''Sunny Hindustani''' is an Indian singer who was the champion of the 11th season of [[Indian Idol]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Indian Idol 11 Grand Finale: Sunny Hindustani is the winner |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/reality-tv/story/indian-idol-11-grand-finale-live-updates-1649265-2020-02-23 |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=India Today |date=23 February 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and career==\nSunny was born in Amarpura Basti in Bhatinda, Punjab in a poor family. He is so much fond of music since his childhood and after being dropped from school he started performing at various functions and events in his locality. He lost his father at the age of 13 and henceforth to earn the livelihood of his family he used to polish shoes at {{rws|Bathinda Junction}}.<ref name=\"Bio\"/>\n\nHe appeared in the audition of [[Indian Idol#Season11|Indian Idol Season 11]] and got selected for the main show. Subsequently in the final, getting most audience votes he became the champion of the Season 11. During the show, he received a few offers from other music composers to playback for them in their upcoming film.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sharma |first1=Yashika |title=Sunny Hindustani: From shoe-polisher to Indian Idol winner, here's the singer's Net Worth |url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/television-news/sunny-hindustani-shoe-polisher-indian-idol-net-worth.html |accessdate=8 April 2020 |work=Republic World |date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=From polishing shoes to winning 'Indian Idol 11' trophy: Fans call Sunny's win a 'VICTORY' |url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/television-news/from-polishing-shoes-to-winning-indian-idol-11-trophy-fans-reaction.html |accessdate=8 April 2020 |work=Republic World}}</ref>\n\nHe made his debut as a playback singer with the song \"Rom Rom\" for the film [[The Body (2019 film)|The Body]].<ref name=\"Body\">{{cite news |title=Indian Idol Contestant Sunny Hindustani Makes Bollywood Singing Debut with Emraan Hashmi's The Body |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/indian-idol-contestant-sunny-hindustani-makes-bollywood-singing-debut-with-emraan-hashmis-the-body-2420161.html |accessdate=8 April 2020 |work=News18 |date=11 December 2019}}</ref> Veteran singer [[Amit Kumar]] also signed him for a song.<ref>{{cite news |title=Singer Amit Kumar signs Indian Idol 11 contestant Sunny Hindustani for a song |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/reality-tv/story/singer-amit-kumar-signs-indian-idol-11-contestant-sunny-hindustani-for-a-song-1629400-2019-12-18 |accessdate=8 April 2020 |work=India Today |agency=IANS |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Year !! Film !! Song !! Composer !! Ref\n|-\n| 2019 || [[The Body (2019 film)|The Body]] || Rom Rom || Shamir Tandon || <ref name=\"Body\"/>\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2020 || [[Panga (film)|Panga]] || Jugnu || [[Shankar\u2013Ehsaan\u2013Loy]] || <ref>{{cite news |title=Indian Idol 11: Sunny Hindustani's Unbelievable Reaction As He Records A Song For Panga With Shankar-Ehsaan-Loy |url=https://www.spotboye.com/television/television-news/indian-idol-11-sunny-hindustani-s-unbelievable-reaction-as-he-records-a-song-for-panga-with-shankar-ehsaan-loy/5e1db663d996471ad814e36f |accessdate=8 April 2020 |work=www.spotboye.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Bad Boy (upcoming film)| Bad Boy]] || Tere Nazar || [[Himesh Reshammiya]] || <ref>{{cite news |title=Himesh Reshammiya signs Sunny Hindustani for a song in Rajkumar Santoshi film |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/reality-tv/story/indian-idol-11-himesh-reshammiya-signs-sunny-hindustani-for-a-song-in-rajkumar-santoshi-film-1625133-2019-12-04 |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Indian Idol}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hindustani, Sunny}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian male singers]]\n[[Category:Indian Idol winners]]\n[[Category:Singers from Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Bollywood playback singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian singers]]\n[[Category:People from Bathinda district]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toT series(link changed toT-Series (company)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunny_Hindustani"}
{"title_page": "Marjaavaan", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Indian Hindi-language action drama film directed by Milap Zaveri}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Marjaavaan\n| image          = Marjaavaan poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| alt            = \n| director       = [[Milap Zaveri]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Bhushan Kumar]]\n* [[Krishan Kumar (actor)|Krishan Kumar]]\n* [[Divya Khosla Kumar]]\n* Monisha Advani\n* Madhu Bhojwani\n* [[Nikkhil Advani]]\n}}\n| writer         = Milap Zaveri\n| starring       = [[Sidharth Malhotra]]<br />[[Riteish Deshmukh]]<br />[[Tara Sutaria]]<br />[[Rakul Preet Singh]]\n| music          = '''Songs:'''<br />[[Tanishk Bagchi]]<br />[[Meet Bros]]<br />[[Payal Dev]]<br />[[Yo Yo Honey Singh]]<br />Aditya Dev<br>[[Sanjoy Chowdhury]]<br>'''Score:'''<br />Sanjoy Chowdhury\n| cinematography = Nigam Bomzan\n| editing        = Maahir Zaveri\n| studio         = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]<br />[[Emmay Entertainment]]\n| distributor    = [[Pen India Limited|PEN Marudhar Cine Entertainment]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2019|11|15}}\n| country        = India\n| runtime        = 135 minutes<ref>{{cite web | url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/marjaavaan-2019 | title=Marjaavan (2019) | website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] | accessdate=13 November 2019}}</ref>\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = \u20b938 crore<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=5735|title=Marjaavaan - Movie - Box Office India|publisher=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=29 March 2020}}</ref>{{small|(Note: Contains print and advertising costs)}}{{better|reason=Box Office India includes print and advertising costs in its figures, which is not done across the globe, where budget refers to the film's cost to produce.|date=March 2020}}\n| gross          = {{Estimation}} {{INR}}65.34 crore<ref name=\"botop\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/marjaavaan/box-office/#bh-movie-box-office|title=Marjaavan Box Office|website=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Marjaavaan''''' ({{translation|I will die}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[Romance film|romantic]] [[action film]] directed by [[Milap Zaveri]] and starring [[Sidharth Malhotra]], [[Riteish Deshmukh]], [[Tara Sutaria]] and [[Rakul Preet Singh]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sidharth-malhotra-riteish-deshmukh-tara-sutaria-in-milap-zaveris-next/articleshow/66436363.cms|title=Riteish Deshmukh, Tara Sutaria, Siddharth Malhotra in Milap Zaveri's next|work=Mumbai Mirror|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sidharth-malhotra-shares-first-look-poster-of-marjaavaan-the-film-will-also-star-tara-sutaria-see-pic/story-KZEho73DPAZg8D0lAjkZSN.html|title=Sidharth Malhotra shares first look poster of Marjaavaan, the film will also star Tara Sutaria. See pic|date=31 October 2018|work=Hindustan times|access-date=1 November 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/tara-sutarias-second-film-after-student-of-the-year-2-marjaavaan-with-sidharth-malhotra-1940529|title=Tara Sutaria's Second Film After Student Of The Year 2&nbsp;\u2013 Marjaavaan With Sidharth Malhotra|work=NDTV.com|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/milap-zaveri-s-next-directorial-titled-marjaavaan-118103100362_1.html|title=Milap Zaveri's next directorial titled 'Marjaavaan'|last=IANS|date=31 October 2018|work=Business Standard India|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/311018/marjaavaan-sidharth-malhotra-to-romance-tara-sutaria-in-milap-zaveri.html|title=Marjaavaan: Sidharth Malhotra to romance Tara Sutaria in Milap Zaveri film|date=31 October 2018|work=Deccan Chronicle|access-date=1 November 2018|language=en}}</ref> The co-producer [[Bhushan Kumar]] described the film as \u201ca violent, dramatic love story\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/marjaavaan-sidharth-malhotra-riteish-deshmukh-tara-sutaria-title-poster-release-photo-5426700/|title=Marjaavaan: Sidharth, Riteish and Tara team up for a violent love story|date=31 October 2018|work=The Indian Express|access-date=1 November 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> After the release date was changed three times, the film was theatrically released in India on 15 November 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sidharth-malhotra-riteish-deshmukh-starrer-marjaavaan-postpone-release-date-to-avert-clash-with-ayushmann-khurranas-bala/amp_articleshow/71536350.cms|title=THE REAL REASON WHY THE MAKERS OF MARJAAVAAN HAVE POSTPONED THE FILM'S RELEASE DATE|date=11 October 2019|work=Mumbai Mirror|access-date=12 November 2019|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/bollywood/story/producer-bhushan-kumar-shifts-release-date-of-marjaavaan-for-ayushmann-khurrana-s-film-bala-1607837-2019-10-10|title=Producer Bhushan Kumar shifts release date of Marjaavaan for Ayushmann Khurrana's film Bala|date=10 October 2019|work=India Today|access-date=12 November 2019|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nRaghu is a loyal goon to the local thug Narayan Anna who controls the water mafia in Mumbai. His father's dependence on Raghu doesn't sit well with Vishnu (Anna's son), whose complexes arise from more than just his short stature, as he is only three feet tall. When Raghu falls for Zoya, a mute musically-inclined [[Kashmiris|Kashmiri]] girl who teaches children music, Vishnu jumps at the opportunity to use it to discredit his father's most favorite goon. \n\nVishnu kidnaps Gaitonde (one of his father's enemies) and tells a kid Zoya had selected for her music festival to shoot him. Zoya sees this and flees but Vishnu is already alerted of her presence. Vishnu tells his father that there was an eyewitness to Gaitonde's murder and that witness is Zoya, so Anna orders Raghu to kill Zoya, not knowing that Raghu loves her. Raghu finds Zoya and tries to run away from Vishnu and his father but Vishnu catches them and orders Raghu, Zoya, and all the kids to be killed. Vishnu's father tells Raghu he and the kids will be safe if he kills only Zoya, as she is the eyewitness to Gaitonde's murder. Zoya tells Raghu to kill her so that he and the kids remain safe. Zoya gives Raghu the gun, places her thumb over his, pulls the tigger and dies in his arms. \n\nThe police arrest a traumatized Raghu for Zoya's murder. In jail, Raghu becomes depressed and broken. Zoya is buried by the children, Raghu's friends and her friends. Vishnu tries to get Raghu killed in jail, knowing if he is released, he will take revenge. However, Raghu beats up the goons Vishnu hired. Vishnu then cuts off Raghu's friend Mazar's leg because Mazar kicked him. When Vishnu's father tells him that Raghu will be sentenced to life, Vishnu helps Raghu get out by [[witness tampering|bribing the proofs]], planning to kill Raghu upon his release.  However, when Raghu returns, Vishnu sees that Raghu is not the same after Zoya's death. His father tells him that Raghu died the day he killed Zoya. Vishnu tries various ways to bring Raghu back to his old ways but fails.Raghu had completely changed and all his old habits had changed. Vishnu's father catches him and warns him against this but Vishnu angrily kills his father and sends goons to kill Raghu. However, Raghu kills them all and buries them. He visits Zoya's grave and vows revenge on Vishnu; he is joined by his friends in this mission.\n\nOn the day of Dussera, when Vishnu comes to burn Ravana's idol, Raghu arrives and starts beating all the goons. Vishnu pierces an arrow into Raghu's heart but Raghu burns him. While dying, Raghu sees Zoya's soul and dies peacefully, surrounded by friends and family. The police arrive and the inspector tells the [[Assistant Commissioner of Police#India|ACP]] that Raghu died. The ACP replies that Raghu returned to his life, which was with Zoya.\n\n== Cast ==\n<!--Do not change cast order. It is as per official poster at 'https://twitter.com/SidMalhotra/status/1057490121279373313'-->\n*[[Sidharth Malhotra]] as Raghuvendra \"Raghu\" Nath: Zoya's love interest\n*[[Riteish Deshmukh]] as Vishnu Shetty: Narayan Anna's son\n*[[Tara Sutaria]] as Zoya Ahmed: Raghu's love interest\n*[[Rakul Preet Singh]] as Aarzoo Hussain\n*[[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]] as Balvesh Shetty / Narayan Anna: Vishnu's father\n*[[Shaad Randhawa]] as Mazhar Khan: Raghu's best friend\n*[[Ravi Kishan]] as ACP Ravi Yadav\n*Om Kanojiya as Timepass\n*[[Anant Jog]] as Zubair Gaitonde: one of Narayan Anna's enemies\n*Amit Mehra as Raamil Gaitonde: Zubair's son\n*[[Varinder Singh Ghuman]] as Rakka\n*[[Bikramjeet Kanwarpal]] as Prison Fighter\n*Godaan Kumar as Shafi\n*Uday Nene as Gopi\n*Alina Kazi as Payal Zehnia: Zoya's friend\n*Swati Seth as Zarika\n*[[Nora Fatehi]] (special appearance in song \"Ek Toh Kum Zindagani\")\n*[[Nushrat Bharucha]] (special appearance in song \"Peeyu Datt Ke\")\n\n== Production ==\n=== Filming ===\nPrincipal photography of the film began on 7 December 2018 with Malhotra sharing his picture on his official Instagram account.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BrE5Q8dhcUp/|title=Sidharth Malhotra on Instagram: \"Ishq aur inteqaam ka koi mazhab nahi, koi ek Rab nahi! ...#Marjaavaan Shoot begins today! @milapzaveri @riteishd @tarasutaria__...\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=12 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://moviealles.com/movies/marjaavaan-movie/|title=Shooting of Marjaavaan Begins|last=|first=|date=12 January 2019|website=Movie Alles|language=en-US|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=12 January 2019}}</ref>\nThe second schedule is set to roll in from mid-January and will end by March. [[Sidharth Malhotra]] is shooting with a dozen goons and has switched to action mode. \"The stunt team wanted to shoot with a body double because Sidharth's back and shoulder would be on fire but he was adamant on doing the scene himself to make it look authentic and stay true to his character\".<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/ritesh-deshmukh-attempts-a-fire-stunt-scene-without-a-body-double-for-marjaavaan/articleshow/67616364.cms|title=Sidharth attempts a fire stunt scene without a body double for Marjaavaan|first=Himesh | last=Mankad | newspaper=Mumbai Mirror |date=21 January 2019 |access-date=14 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sidharth-malhotra-starrer-marjaavaan-shoot-begins-5483118|title=Ritesh Deshmukh starrer Marjaavaan commences shooting|access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref> Siddharth wrapped up his portion except for songs on 15 March 2019. He announced the news by posting a picture with crews with a heartfelt message.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/its-a-wrap-sidharth-malhotra-winds-up-the-shoot-of-marjaavaan-shares-pics-from-the-sets/383208|website=Times Now News 18|title=It's a wrap! Sidharth Malhotra winds up the shoot of Marjaavaan; shares pics from the sets|first=Shalini|last=Singh|date=15 March 2019|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, Deshmukh revealed that [[Shah Rukh Khan]] had helped the production team with some VFX shots for the former's role as a dwarf.<ref>{{cite news |title=Shah Rukh Khan helped team Marjaavaan with certain VFX shots for Riteish Deshmukh's role as a dwarf! : Bollywood News - Bollywood Hungama |url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/shah-rukh-khan-helped-team-marjaavaan-certain-vfx-shots-riteish-deshmukhs-role-dwarf/ |accessdate=13 November 2019 |work=Bollywood Hungama |date=13 November 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Marketing and release ==\nThe official poster of the film was shared by Sidharth Malhotra on 30 October 2018, announcing the release date of 8 November 2019. On 5 August 2019, Malhotra announced that the film is delayed to avoid the clash with [[Siddharth Anand]]'s big budget film  ''[[War (2019 film)|War]]'' starring [[Tiger Shroff]] and [[Hrithik Roshan]], but the release date was not  confirmed. On 23 August 2019, the first poster was unveiled by Malhotra, giving the new release date of 8 November 2019. On 3 September, a second poster was unveiled, in which it was shown that the release date of the film is advanced to 8 November.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=SidMalhotra |author=[[Sidharth Malhotra]] |number=1169815105095077889 |date=6 September 2019 |title=Taareekh nayi hai lekin anjaam wahi hoga. Ishq mein maarenge bhi aur marenge bhi. Milte hain 8th Nov ko. #Marjaavaan|accessdate=6 September 2019 }}</ref> on 10 October, he announced new release date of film is 15 November 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=SidMalhotra |author=[[Sidharth Malhotra]] |number=1182158735231406081|date=10 October 2019 |title=Thodi der se aayenge par maarenge bhi aur marenge bhi! #Marjaavaan will now release on 15th November 2019.|accessdate=12 November 2019 }}</ref>\n\nThe official trailer of the film was launched on 26 September 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=L7TbPUOn1hc|title = Official Trailer: Marjaavaan \u2013 Riteish Deshmukh, Sidharth Malhotra,Tara Sutaria \u2013 Milap Zaveri|publisher=[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]|website=YouTube|date=26 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/marjaavaan-trailer-sidharth-malhotra-and-riteish-deshmukh-starrer-is-high-on-action-drama-but-suffers-ek-villain-hangover/articleshow/71308470.cms|title='Marjaavaan' trailer: Riteish Deshmukh's dwarf avatar stands out in this high octane action drama starring Sidharth Malhotra \u2013 Times of India \u25ba|website=The Times of India|date=26 September 2019|accessdate=26 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/marjaavan-trailer-out-sidharth-malhotra-and-riteish-deshmukh-return-in-ek-villain-2-0-1603433-2019-09-26|title=Marjaavaan trailer out: Sidharth Malhotra and Riteish Deshmukh return in Ek Villain 2.0|website=India Today|date=26 September 2019|accessdate=26 September 2019}}</ref> The official second trailer of the film was launched on 1 November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=OpqbtG-dnqQ|title =Marjaavaan Trailer 2 - Riteish Deshmukh, Sidharth Malhotra,Tara Sutaria, Rakul Preet - Milap Zaveri|publisher=[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]|website=YouTube|date=1 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe film was released on 15 November 2019 after the release date was advanced by a week to accommodate the release of ''[[Bala (2019 film)|Bala]]''.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=itsBhushanKumar| author= Bhushan Kumar|date = 10 October 2019|number=1182157955413598208?s=19| title =I\u2019ve had a long standing relationship with @MaddockFilms and #DineshVijan is also a personal friend. I\u2019ve decided to shift #Marjaavaan to 15th November 2019, to make way for #Bala. My best wishes to the team! @TSeries}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/sidharth-malhotras-marjaavaan-release-postponed-to-avert-clash-with-ayushmann-khurranas-bala/amp_articleshow/71533741.cms|title=Sidharth Malhotra's 'Marjaavaan' release postponed to avert clash with Ayushmann Khurrana's 'Bala|website=The Times of India|date=11 October 2019|accessdate=12 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''Khaleej Times'' rated the film 1.5 stars out of 5 and said, \"'Marjaavan' falls several shades short of a proper Bollywood masala entertainer that it aspires to in spite of having all the ingredients for it. The weak and cliched plotline along with heavy-duty dialogues that should have impressed but end up sounding hollow is only part of the problem.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/bollywood/marjaavaan-movie-review-all-talk-and-no-impact | title='Marjaavaan' movie review: All talk and no impact}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Times of India]]'' rated the film 2.5 stars out of 5 and reviewed, \"Marjaavaan attempts to check all the boxes for an emotional action rollercoaster, but its dated execution doesn\u2019t quite make the kill.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/marjaavaan/movie-review/72057247.cms |title = Marjaavaan Movie Review &#123;2.5/5&#125;: Nothing to die for}}</ref>\n\n''[[Mumbai Mirror]]'' rated the film 2 on 5 stars and said, \"This Sidharth Malthotra, Riteish Deshmukh and Tara Sutaria-starrer is a tedious watch.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-review/marjaavaan-movie-review-this-sidharth-malthotra-riteish-deshmukh-tara-sutaria-starrer-is-a-tedious-watch/articleshow/72063458.cms | title=Marjaavaan Movie Review: This Sidharth Malthotra, Riteish Deshmukh and Tara Sutaria-starrer is a tedious watch}}</ref>\n\n''[[Scroll.in]]'' rated the film 2 out of 5 stars and wrote, \"A 1980s Bollywood flashback with characters who are cardboard cutouts.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://scroll.in/reel/943495/marjaavaan-movie-review-a-1980s-bollywood-flashback-with-characters-who-are-cardboard-cutouts | title='Marjaavaan' movie review: A 1980s Bollywood flashback with characters who are cardboard cutouts}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''Marjaavaan''{{'}}s opening day domestic collection was {{INR}}7.03 crore. On the second day, the film collected {{INR}}7.21 crore. On the third day, the film collected {{INR}}10.18 crore, taking total opening weekend collection to {{INR}}24.42 crore.<ref name=\"botop\" />\n\n{{As of|2019|12|16}}, with a gross of {{INR}}56.88 crore in India and {{INR}}8.46 crore overseas, the film has a worldwide gross collection of {{INR}}65.34 crore.<ref name=\"botop\" />\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Marjaavaan\n| type       = Soundtrack \n| artist     = [[Tanishk Bagchi]], [[Meet Bros]], [[Payal Dev]], [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]], Aditya Dev and [[Sanjoy Chowdhury]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 27 November 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiosaavn.com/album/marjaavaan/tcbfgbFQNZE_|title=Marjaavaan - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack |publisher=Jio Saavn|accessdate=19 January 2020}}</ref>\n| recorded   = 2018\u201319\n| venue      =\n| studio     = \n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 46:39\n| label      = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| language   = Hindi\n| producer   =  [[Bhushan Kumar]]\n| misc       = {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|qk7cybeLS_c|Official Audio CD Jukebox}}\n}}}}\n\nThis music of film is composed by [[Tanishk Bagchi]], [[Meet Bros]], [[Payal Dev]], [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]], Aditya Dev and [[Sanjoy Chowdhury]] with lyrics written by [[Kumaar]], [[Tanishk Bagchi]], Kunaal Vermaa, [[Manoj Muntashir]], [[A. M. Turaz]], [[Rashmi Virag]], [[Prasoon Joshi]], Yo Yo Honey Singh, Dope Leo and Mujtaba Aziz Naza. The second song \"Ek Toh Kum Zindagani\" is a remake of the song \"Pyar Do Pyar Lo\" from the film [[Janbaaz]], being the second remake of the song after Anees Bazmee's ''[[Thank You (2011 film)|Thank You]]'', where it was composed by [[Pritam]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodlife.com/video-gallery/marjaavaan-song-ek-toh-kum-zindagani-teaser-nora-fatehi-and-tanishk-bagchi-to-spin-rekhas-pyar-do-pyar-lo-1492988/amp/|title=Marjaavaan song Ek Toh Kum Zindagani teaser: Nora Fatehi and Tanishk Bagchi to spin Rekha's Pyar Do Pyar Lo|website=Bollywood Life|date=8 October 2019|access-date=8 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/amp/entertainment/bollywood/marjaavaan-pyaar-do-pyaar-lo-nora-fatehi-sizzles-in-another-remake-555115|title=Marjaavaan's Pyaar Do Pyaar Lo: Nora Fatehi sizzles in another remake|website=India Tv |date=8 October 2019|access-date=8 October 2019}}</ref> The fourth song Haiya Ho, is a remake of \"Chahe Meri Jaan Tu Le Le\", a song from [[Dayavan]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/marjaavaan-song-haiya-ho-rakul-preet-singh-woos-a-grieving-sidharth-malhotra-in-yet-another-recreated-number-watch/story-jZPpmkoBYMPrEObJsU5E0J.html|title=Marjaavaan song Haiya Ho: Rakul Preet Singh woos a grieving Sidharth Malhotra in yet another recreated number. Watch|date=26 October 2019|website=Hindustan Times|accessdate=19 December 2019}}</ref>. Two songs of the film which were removed from the final cut were released later as singles as they didn't go well with the narrative of the film. They were the song \"Peeyu Datt Ke\", starring [[Nushrat Bharucha]] which was released on 2 December 2019 and the song \"Masakali 2.0\" which is a recreated version of the song \"Masakali\" from the 2009 film [[Delhi-6]] and was released on 8 April 2020 by [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]].\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline=Track listing\n| extra_column=Singer(s)\n| total_length= 46:39\n| title1   = [[Tum Hi Aana]]\n| extra1   = [[Jubin Nautiyal]]\n| music1   = [[Payal Dev]]\n| lyrics1  = Kunaal Vermaa\n| length1  = 4:09\n| title2   = Ek Toh Kum Zindagani\n| extra2   = [[Neha Kakkar]], [[Yash Narvekar]]\n| music2   = [[Tanishk Bagchi]]\n| lyrics2  = Tanishk Bagchi, [[A. M. Turaz]]\n| length2  = 3:10\n| title3   = Thodi Jagah\n| extra3   = [[Arijit Singh]]\n| music3   = Tanishk Bagchi\n| lyrics3  = [[Rashmi Virag]]\n| length3  = 3:38\n| title4   = Haiya Ho\n| extra4   = [[Tulsi Kumar]], Jubin Nautiyal \n| music4   = Tanishk Bagchi\n| lyrics4  = Tanishk Bagchi\n| length4  = 2:50\n| title5   = Kinna Sona\n| extra5   = Jubin Nautiyal, [[Dhvani Bhanushali]]\n| music5   = [[Meet Bros]]\n| lyrics5  = [[Kumaar]]\n| length5  = 4:33\n| title6   = Raghupati Raghav Raja Ram\n| extra6   = [[Palak Muchhal]]\n| music6   = Tanishk Bagchi\n| lyrics6  = [[Manoj Muntashir]]\n| length6  = 3:28\n| title7   = Hasbi Rabbi\n| extra7   = Altamash Faridi, [[Kamaal Khan]]\n| music7   = Aditya Dev\n| lyrics7  = Traditional\n| length7  = 5:04\n| title8   = Tum Hi Aana\n| note8    = Sad Version\n| extra8   = [[Jubin Nautiyal]]\n| music8   = Payal Dev\n| lyrics8  = Kunaal Vermaa\n| length8  = 1:23\n| title9   = Thodi Jagah\n| note9    = Female Version\n| extra9   = [[Tulsi Kumar]]\n| music9   = Tanishk Bagchi\n| lyrics9  = [[Rashmi Virag]]\n| length9  = 3:36\n| title10  = Tum Hi Aana\n| note10   = Duet Version \n| extra10  = Jubin Nautiyal, [[Dhvani Bhanushali]]\n| music10  = [[Payal Dev]]\n| lyrics10 = Kunaal Vermaa\n| length10 = 4:08\n| title11  = Hasbi Rabbi Naat\n| extra11  = Mujtaba Aziz Naza \n| music11  = [[Sanjoy Chowdhury]]\n| lyrics11 = Mujtaba Aziz Naza \n| length11 = 1:11\n| title12  = Tum Hi Aana\n| note12   = Happy Version\n| extra12  = Jubin Nautiyal\n| music12  = Payal Dev\n| lyrics12 = Kunaal Vermaa\n| length12 = 2:49\n| title13  = Peeyu Datt Ke\n| extra13  = [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]], [[Ritu Pathak]]\n| music13  = Yo Yo Honey Singh\n| lyrics13 = Yo Yo Honey Singh, Dope Leo\n| length13 = 3:48\n| title14  = Masakali 2.0\n| extra14  = [[Sachet-Parampara|Sachet Tandon]], Tulsi Kumar\n| music14  = Tanishk Bagchi\n| lyrics14 = [[Prasoon Joshi]]\n| length14 = 2:52\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{IMDb title|tt9248934}}\n*[https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/marjaavaan/ ''Marjaavaan''] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n*{{Rotten Tomatoes|marjaavaan}}\n\n{{Milap Zaveri}}\n{{Portal bar|India|Film|Bollywood}}\n\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:2010s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian action films]]\n[[Category:Indian romance films]]\n[[Category:Romantic action films]]\n[[Category:Indian films about revenge]]\n[[Category:Masala films]]\n[[Category:T-Series films]]\n[[Category:Films about deaf people]]\n[[Category:Films about rape in India]]\n[[Category:Films about terrorism in India]]\n[[Category:Works about dwarfism]]\n[[Category:2010s vigilante films]]\n[[Category:Indian vigilante films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 Indian Hindi-language action drama film directed by Milap Zaveri}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Marjaavaan\n| image          = Marjaavaan poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| alt            = \n| director       = [[Milap Zaveri]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Bhushan Kumar]]\n* [[Krishan Kumar (actor)|Krishan Kumar]]\n* [[Divya Khosla Kumar]]\n* Monisha Advani\n* Madhu Bhojwani\n* [[Nikkhil Advani]]\n}}\n| writer         = Milap Zaveri\n| starring       = [[Sidharth Malhotra]]<br />[[Riteish Deshmukh]]<br />[[Tara Sutaria]]<br />[[Rakul Preet Singh]]\n| music          = '''Songs:'''<br />[[Tanishk Bagchi]]<br />[[Meet Bros]]<br />[[Payal Dev]]<br />[[Yo Yo Honey Singh]]<br />Aditya Dev<br>[[Sanjoy Chowdhury]]<br>'''Score:'''<br />Sanjoy Chowdhury\n| cinematography = Nigam Bomzan\n| editing        = Maahir Zaveri\n| studio         = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]<br />[[Emmay Entertainment]]\n| distributor    = [[Pen India Limited|PEN Marudhar Cine Entertainment]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2019|11|15}}\n| country        = India\n| runtime        = 135 minutes<ref>{{cite web | url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/marjaavaan-2019 | title=Marjaavan (2019) | website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] | accessdate=13 November 2019}}</ref>\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = \u20b938 crore<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=5735|title=Marjaavaan - Movie - Box Office India|publisher=[[Box Office India]]|accessdate=29 March 2020}}</ref>{{small|(Note: Contains print and advertising costs)}}{{better|reason=Box Office India includes print and advertising costs in its figures, which is not done across the globe, where budget refers to the film's cost to produce.|date=March 2020}}\n| gross          = {{Estimation}} {{INR}}65.34 crore<ref name=\"botop\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/marjaavaan/box-office/#bh-movie-box-office|title=Marjaavan Box Office|website=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Marjaavaan''''' ({{translation|I will die}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[Romance film|romantic]] [[action film]] directed by [[Milap Zaveri]] and starring [[Sidharth Malhotra]], [[Riteish Deshmukh]], [[Tara Sutaria]] and [[Rakul Preet Singh]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sidharth-malhotra-riteish-deshmukh-tara-sutaria-in-milap-zaveris-next/articleshow/66436363.cms|title=Riteish Deshmukh, Tara Sutaria, Siddharth Malhotra in Milap Zaveri's next|work=Mumbai Mirror|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/sidharth-malhotra-shares-first-look-poster-of-marjaavaan-the-film-will-also-star-tara-sutaria-see-pic/story-KZEho73DPAZg8D0lAjkZSN.html|title=Sidharth Malhotra shares first look poster of Marjaavaan, the film will also star Tara Sutaria. See pic|date=31 October 2018|work=Hindustan times|access-date=1 November 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/tara-sutarias-second-film-after-student-of-the-year-2-marjaavaan-with-sidharth-malhotra-1940529|title=Tara Sutaria's Second Film After Student Of The Year 2&nbsp;\u2013 Marjaavaan With Sidharth Malhotra|work=NDTV.com|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/milap-zaveri-s-next-directorial-titled-marjaavaan-118103100362_1.html|title=Milap Zaveri's next directorial titled 'Marjaavaan'|last=IANS|date=31 October 2018|work=Business Standard India|access-date=1 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/bollywood/311018/marjaavaan-sidharth-malhotra-to-romance-tara-sutaria-in-milap-zaveri.html|title=Marjaavaan: Sidharth Malhotra to romance Tara Sutaria in Milap Zaveri film|date=31 October 2018|work=Deccan Chronicle|access-date=1 November 2018|language=en}}</ref> The co-producer [[Bhushan Kumar]] described the film as \u201ca violent, dramatic love story\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/marjaavaan-sidharth-malhotra-riteish-deshmukh-tara-sutaria-title-poster-release-photo-5426700/|title=Marjaavaan: Sidharth, Riteish and Tara team up for a violent love story|date=31 October 2018|work=The Indian Express|access-date=1 November 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> After the release date was changed three times, the film was theatrically released in India on 15 November 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/sidharth-malhotra-riteish-deshmukh-starrer-marjaavaan-postpone-release-date-to-avert-clash-with-ayushmann-khurranas-bala/amp_articleshow/71536350.cms|title=THE REAL REASON WHY THE MAKERS OF MARJAAVAAN HAVE POSTPONED THE FILM'S RELEASE DATE|date=11 October 2019|work=Mumbai Mirror|access-date=12 November 2019|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/bollywood/story/producer-bhushan-kumar-shifts-release-date-of-marjaavaan-for-ayushmann-khurrana-s-film-bala-1607837-2019-10-10|title=Producer Bhushan Kumar shifts release date of Marjaavaan for Ayushmann Khurrana's film Bala|date=10 October 2019|work=India Today|access-date=12 November 2019|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nRaghu is a loyal goon to the local thug Narayan Anna who controls the water mafia in Mumbai. His father's dependence on Raghu doesn't sit well with Vishnu (Anna's son), whose complexes arise from more than just his short stature, as he is only three feet tall. When Raghu falls for Zoya, a mute musically-inclined [[Kashmiris|Kashmiri]] girl who teaches children music, Vishnu jumps at the opportunity to use it to discredit his father's most favorite goon. \n\nVishnu kidnaps Gaitonde (one of his father's enemies) and tells a kid Zoya had selected for her music festival to shoot him. Zoya sees this and flees but Vishnu is already alerted of her presence. Vishnu tells his father that there was an eyewitness to Gaitonde's murder and that witness is Zoya, so Anna orders Raghu to kill Zoya, not knowing that Raghu loves her. Raghu finds Zoya and tries to run away from Vishnu and his father but Vishnu catches them and orders Raghu, Zoya, and all the kids to be killed. Vishnu's father tells Raghu he and the kids will be safe if he kills only Zoya, as she is the eyewitness to Gaitonde's murder. Zoya tells Raghu to kill her so that he and the kids remain safe. Zoya gives Raghu the gun, places her thumb over his, pulls the tigger and dies in his arms. \n\nThe police arrest a traumatized Raghu for Zoya's murder. In jail, Raghu becomes depressed and broken. Zoya is buried by the children, Raghu's friends and her friends. Vishnu tries to get Raghu killed in jail, knowing if he is released, he will take revenge. However, Raghu beats up the goons Vishnu hired. Vishnu then cuts off Raghu's friend Mazar's leg because Mazar kicked him. When Vishnu's father tells him that Raghu will be sentenced to life, Vishnu helps Raghu get out by [[witness tampering|bribing the proofs]], planning to kill Raghu upon his release.  However, when Raghu returns, Vishnu sees that Raghu is not the same after Zoya's death. His father tells him that Raghu died the day he killed Zoya. Vishnu tries various ways to bring Raghu back to his old ways but fails.Raghu had completely changed and all his old habits had changed. Vishnu's father catches him and warns him against this but Vishnu angrily kills his father and sends goons to kill Raghu. However, Raghu kills them all and buries them. He visits Zoya's grave and vows revenge on Vishnu; he is joined by his friends in this mission.\n\nOn the day of Dussera, when Vishnu comes to burn Ravana's idol, Raghu arrives and starts beating all the goons. Vishnu pierces an arrow into Raghu's heart but Raghu burns him. While dying, Raghu sees Zoya's soul and dies peacefully, surrounded by friends and family. The police arrive and the inspector tells the [[Assistant Commissioner of Police#India|ACP]] that Raghu died. The ACP replies that Raghu returned to his life, which was with Zoya.\n\n== Cast ==\n<!--Do not change cast order. It is as per official poster at 'https://twitter.com/SidMalhotra/status/1057490121279373313'-->\n*[[Sidharth Malhotra]] as Raghuvendra \"Raghu\" Nath: Zoya's love interest\n*[[Riteish Deshmukh]] as Vishnu Shetty: Narayan Anna's son\n*[[Tara Sutaria]] as Zoya Ahmed: Raghu's love interest\n*[[Rakul Preet Singh]] as Aarzoo Hussain\n*[[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]] as Balvesh Shetty / Narayan Anna: Vishnu's father\n*[[Shaad Randhawa]] as Mazhar Khan: Raghu's best friend\n*[[Ravi Kishan]] as ACP Ravi Yadav\n*Om Kanojiya as Timepass\n*[[Anant Jog]] as Zubair Gaitonde: one of Narayan Anna's enemies\n*Amit Mehra as Raamil Gaitonde: Zubair's son\n*[[Varinder Singh Ghuman]] as Rakka\n*[[Bikramjeet Kanwarpal]] as Prison Fighter\n*Godaan Kumar as Shafi\n*Uday Nene as Gopi\n*Alina Kazi as Payal Zehnia: Zoya's friend\n*Swati Seth as Zarika\n*[[Nora Fatehi]] (special appearance in song \"Ek Toh Kum Zindagani\")\n*[[Nushrat Bharucha]] (special appearance in song \"Peeyu Datt Ke\")\n\n== Production ==\n=== Filming ===\nPrincipal photography of the film began on 7 December 2018 with Malhotra sharing his picture on his official Instagram account.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BrE5Q8dhcUp/|title=Sidharth Malhotra on Instagram: \"Ishq aur inteqaam ka koi mazhab nahi, koi ek Rab nahi! ...#Marjaavaan Shoot begins today! @milapzaveri @riteishd @tarasutaria__...\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=12 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://moviealles.com/movies/marjaavaan-movie/|title=Shooting of Marjaavaan Begins|last=|first=|date=12 January 2019|website=Movie Alles|language=en-US|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=12 January 2019}}</ref>\nThe second schedule is set to roll in from mid-January and will end by March. [[Sidharth Malhotra]] is shooting with a dozen goons and has switched to action mode. \"The stunt team wanted to shoot with a body double because Sidharth's back and shoulder would be on fire but he was adamant on doing the scene himself to make it look authentic and stay true to his character\".<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/ritesh-deshmukh-attempts-a-fire-stunt-scene-without-a-body-double-for-marjaavaan/articleshow/67616364.cms|title=Sidharth attempts a fire stunt scene without a body double for Marjaavaan|first=Himesh | last=Mankad | newspaper=Mumbai Mirror |date=21 January 2019 |access-date=14 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/sidharth-malhotra-starrer-marjaavaan-shoot-begins-5483118|title=Ritesh Deshmukh starrer Marjaavaan commences shooting|access-date=8 December 2018}}</ref> Siddharth wrapped up his portion except for songs on 15 March 2019. He announced the news by posting a picture with crews with a heartfelt message.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/its-a-wrap-sidharth-malhotra-winds-up-the-shoot-of-marjaavaan-shares-pics-from-the-sets/383208|website=Times Now News 18|title=It's a wrap! Sidharth Malhotra winds up the shoot of Marjaavaan; shares pics from the sets|first=Shalini|last=Singh|date=15 March 2019|access-date=21 March 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, Deshmukh revealed that [[Shah Rukh Khan]] had helped the production team with some VFX shots for the former's role as a dwarf.<ref>{{cite news |title=Shah Rukh Khan helped team Marjaavaan with certain VFX shots for Riteish Deshmukh's role as a dwarf! : Bollywood News - Bollywood Hungama |url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/shah-rukh-khan-helped-team-marjaavaan-certain-vfx-shots-riteish-deshmukhs-role-dwarf/ |accessdate=13 November 2019 |work=Bollywood Hungama |date=13 November 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Marketing and release ==\nThe official poster of the film was shared by Sidharth Malhotra on 30 October 2018, announcing the release date of 8 November 2019. On 5 August 2019, Malhotra announced that the film is delayed to avoid the clash with [[Siddharth Anand]]'s big budget film  ''[[War (2019 film)|War]]'' starring [[Tiger Shroff]] and [[Hrithik Roshan]], but the release date was not  confirmed. On 23 August 2019, the first poster was unveiled by Malhotra, giving the new release date of 8 November 2019. On 3 September, a second poster was unveiled, in which it was shown that the release date of the film is advanced to 8 November.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=SidMalhotra |author=[[Sidharth Malhotra]] |number=1169815105095077889 |date=6 September 2019 |title=Taareekh nayi hai lekin anjaam wahi hoga. Ishq mein maarenge bhi aur marenge bhi. Milte hain 8th Nov ko. #Marjaavaan|accessdate=6 September 2019 }}</ref> on 10 October, he announced new release date of film is 15 November 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet |user=SidMalhotra |author=[[Sidharth Malhotra]] |number=1182158735231406081|date=10 October 2019 |title=Thodi der se aayenge par maarenge bhi aur marenge bhi! #Marjaavaan will now release on 15th November 2019.|accessdate=12 November 2019 }}</ref>\n\nThe official trailer of the film was launched on 26 September 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=L7TbPUOn1hc|title = Official Trailer: Marjaavaan \u2013 Riteish Deshmukh, Sidharth Malhotra,Tara Sutaria \u2013 Milap Zaveri|publisher=[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]|website=YouTube|date=26 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/marjaavaan-trailer-sidharth-malhotra-and-riteish-deshmukh-starrer-is-high-on-action-drama-but-suffers-ek-villain-hangover/articleshow/71308470.cms|title='Marjaavaan' trailer: Riteish Deshmukh's dwarf avatar stands out in this high octane action drama starring Sidharth Malhotra \u2013 Times of India \u25ba|website=The Times of India|date=26 September 2019|accessdate=26 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/marjaavan-trailer-out-sidharth-malhotra-and-riteish-deshmukh-return-in-ek-villain-2-0-1603433-2019-09-26|title=Marjaavaan trailer out: Sidharth Malhotra and Riteish Deshmukh return in Ek Villain 2.0|website=India Today|date=26 September 2019|accessdate=26 September 2019}}</ref> The official second trailer of the film was launched on 1 November 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=OpqbtG-dnqQ|title =Marjaavaan Trailer 2 - Riteish Deshmukh, Sidharth Malhotra,Tara Sutaria, Rakul Preet - Milap Zaveri|publisher=[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]|website=YouTube|date=1 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe film was released on 15 November 2019 after the release date was advanced by a week to accommodate the release of ''[[Bala (2019 film)|Bala]]''.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=itsBhushanKumar| author= Bhushan Kumar|date = 10 October 2019|number=1182157955413598208?s=19| title =I\u2019ve had a long standing relationship with @MaddockFilms and #DineshVijan is also a personal friend. I\u2019ve decided to shift #Marjaavaan to 15th November 2019, to make way for #Bala. My best wishes to the team! @TSeries}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/sidharth-malhotras-marjaavaan-release-postponed-to-avert-clash-with-ayushmann-khurranas-bala/amp_articleshow/71533741.cms|title=Sidharth Malhotra's 'Marjaavaan' release postponed to avert clash with Ayushmann Khurrana's 'Bala|website=The Times of India|date=11 October 2019|accessdate=12 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''Khaleej Times'' rated the film 1.5 stars out of 5 and said, \"'Marjaavan' falls several shades short of a proper Bollywood masala entertainer that it aspires to in spite of having all the ingredients for it. The weak and cliched plotline along with heavy-duty dialogues that should have impressed but end up sounding hollow is only part of the problem.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/bollywood/marjaavaan-movie-review-all-talk-and-no-impact | title='Marjaavaan' movie review: All talk and no impact}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Times of India]]'' rated the film 2.5 stars out of 5 and reviewed, \"Marjaavaan attempts to check all the boxes for an emotional action rollercoaster, but its dated execution doesn\u2019t quite make the kill.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/marjaavaan/movie-review/72057247.cms |title = Marjaavaan Movie Review &#123;2.5/5&#125;: Nothing to die for}}</ref>\n\n''[[Mumbai Mirror]]'' rated the film 2 on 5 stars and said, \"This Sidharth Malthotra, Riteish Deshmukh and Tara Sutaria-starrer is a tedious watch.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-review/marjaavaan-movie-review-this-sidharth-malthotra-riteish-deshmukh-tara-sutaria-starrer-is-a-tedious-watch/articleshow/72063458.cms | title=Marjaavaan Movie Review: This Sidharth Malthotra, Riteish Deshmukh and Tara Sutaria-starrer is a tedious watch}}</ref>\n\n''[[Scroll.in]]'' rated the film 2 out of 5 stars and wrote, \"A 1980s Bollywood flashback with characters who are cardboard cutouts.\"<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://scroll.in/reel/943495/marjaavaan-movie-review-a-1980s-bollywood-flashback-with-characters-who-are-cardboard-cutouts | title='Marjaavaan' movie review: A 1980s Bollywood flashback with characters who are cardboard cutouts}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''Marjaavaan''{{'}}s opening day domestic collection was {{INR}}7.03 crore. On the second day, the film collected {{INR}}7.21 crore. On the third day, the film collected {{INR}}10.18 crore, taking total opening weekend collection to {{INR}}24.42 crore.<ref name=\"botop\" />\n\n{{As of|2019|12|16}}, with a gross of {{INR}}56.88 crore in India and {{INR}}8.46 crore overseas, the film has a worldwide gross collection of {{INR}}65.34 crore.<ref name=\"botop\" />\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Marjaavaan\n| type       = Soundtrack \n| artist     = [[Tanishk Bagchi]], [[Meet Bros]], [[Payal Dev]], [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]], Aditya Dev and [[Sanjoy Chowdhury]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 27 November 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiosaavn.com/album/marjaavaan/tcbfgbFQNZE_|title=Marjaavaan - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack |publisher=Jio Saavn|accessdate=19 January 2020}}</ref>\n| recorded   = 2018\u201319\n| venue      =\n| studio     = \n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 46:39\n| label      = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| language   = Hindi\n| producer   =  [[Bhushan Kumar]]\n| misc       = {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|qk7cybeLS_c|Official Audio CD Jukebox}}\n}}}}\n\nThis music of film is composed by [[Tanishk Bagchi]], [[Meet Bros]], [[Payal Dev]], [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]], Aditya Dev and [[Sanjoy Chowdhury]] with lyrics written by [[Kumaar]], [[Tanishk Bagchi]], Kunaal Vermaa, [[Manoj Muntashir]], [[A. M. Turaz]], [[Rashmi Virag]], [[Prasoon Joshi]], Yo Yo Honey Singh, Dope Leo and Mujtaba Aziz Naza. The second song \"Ek Toh Kum Zindagani\" is a remake of the song \"Pyar Do Pyar Lo\" from the film [[Janbaaz]], being the second remake of the song after Anees Bazmee's ''[[Thank You (2011 film)|Thank You]]'', where it was composed by [[Pritam]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodlife.com/video-gallery/marjaavaan-song-ek-toh-kum-zindagani-teaser-nora-fatehi-and-tanishk-bagchi-to-spin-rekhas-pyar-do-pyar-lo-1492988/amp/|title=Marjaavaan song Ek Toh Kum Zindagani teaser: Nora Fatehi and Tanishk Bagchi to spin Rekha's Pyar Do Pyar Lo|website=Bollywood Life|date=8 October 2019|access-date=8 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/amp/entertainment/bollywood/marjaavaan-pyaar-do-pyaar-lo-nora-fatehi-sizzles-in-another-remake-555115|title=Marjaavaan's Pyaar Do Pyaar Lo: Nora Fatehi sizzles in another remake|website=India Tv |date=8 October 2019|access-date=8 October 2019}}</ref> The fourth song Haiya Ho, is a remake of \"Chahe Meri Jaan Tu Le Le\", a song from [[Dayavan]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/marjaavaan-song-haiya-ho-rakul-preet-singh-woos-a-grieving-sidharth-malhotra-in-yet-another-recreated-number-watch/story-jZPpmkoBYMPrEObJsU5E0J.html|title=Marjaavaan song Haiya Ho: Rakul Preet Singh woos a grieving Sidharth Malhotra in yet another recreated number. Watch|date=26 October 2019|website=Hindustan Times|accessdate=19 December 2019}}</ref>. Two songs of the film which were removed from the final cut were released later as singles as they didn't go well with the narrative of the film. They were the song \"Peeyu Datt Ke\", starring [[Nushrat Bharucha]] which was released on 2 December 2019 and the song \"Masakali 2.0\" which is a recreated version of the song \"Masakali\" from the 2009 film [[Delhi-6]] and was released on 8 April 2020 by [[T-Series]].\n\n{{Tracklist\n| headline=Track listing\n| extra_column=Singer(s)\n| total_length= 46:39\n| title1   = [[Tum Hi Aana]]\n| extra1   = [[Jubin Nautiyal]]\n| music1   = [[Payal Dev]]\n| lyrics1  = Kunaal Vermaa\n| length1  = 4:09\n| title2   = Ek Toh Kum Zindagani\n| extra2   = [[Neha Kakkar]], [[Yash Narvekar]]\n| music2   = [[Tanishk Bagchi]]\n| lyrics2  = Tanishk Bagchi, [[A. M. Turaz]]\n| length2  = 3:10\n| title3   = Thodi Jagah\n| extra3   = [[Arijit Singh]]\n| music3   = Tanishk Bagchi\n| lyrics3  = [[Rashmi Virag]]\n| length3  = 3:38\n| title4   = Haiya Ho\n| extra4   = [[Tulsi Kumar]], Jubin Nautiyal \n| musi